    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the tree belonging to the species Alnus glutinosa, native to Europe, the British Isles and Africa. It is dull, light reddish-brown in color and is used for making broom and brush backs, hat blocks, toys, and wooden shoes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
